snippet: The market for Jason Collins, who came out in April, seems to have shrunk, partly because of his modest career statistics, his veteran’s salary and the N.B.A.’s luxury tax threshold.
abstract: Jason Collins has been widely praised since announcing that he is a gay professional basketball player, but he is still waiting for a call from an NBA team; center says he is not dismissing the idea that, despite being a marginal player with modest career statistics, something more sinister is behind fact that he has not been signed as a free agent.
lead_paragraph: The market for Jason Collins, who came out in April, seems to have shrunk, partly because of his modest career statistics, his veteran’s salary and the N.B.A.’s luxury tax threshold.

headline.main: Jason Collins, Openly Gay and Still Unsigned, Waits and Wonders
headline.print_headline: After Announcing He’s Gay, a Player Still Lacks a Team
